<head>STUDY</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">學</item><item xml:lang="och">學</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>INVESTIGATE THINGS OR IMITATE ANOTHER so as to STRIVE FOR SKILLFULNESS, KNOWING AND UNDERSTANDING.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The dominant word is xué 學 (ant. jiào 教 "train teach")which refers primarily to studying or training under another person, and secondarily to the learning by heart texts. Very often, the word retains a tinge of immitation.</p>
<p>2. Shī 師 and cóng 從 refer to deciding to study under someone and treating him as one's teacher.</p>
<p>3. Kǎo 考 refers to an investigation of a subject in a "scientific" spirit.</p>
<p>4. Jiū 究 and yán 研 refers to an in-depth study of a subject, typically involving a fair amount of reflection.</p>
<p>5. Zhì 治 and gōng 攻 refer to the specialised study, typically of a certain text.</p>
<p>6. Xí 習 refers to rehearsal of what one has learnt, through repetition of text and/or through enactment in practice.</p></div>
